# Incident Runbook: {{ .Service.Name }}

## Ownership

- Team: {{ .Service.Team }}
- Owner: {{ .Service.Owner }}
- Namespace: {{ .Service.Namespace }}
- Environment: {{ .Service.Environment }}

## SLO

- Availability target: {{ printf "%.2f" .Service.SLOTarget }}%
- P99 latency objective: 300ms
- Error-rate rollback threshold: 1%
- Deployment strategy: {{ .Service.DeploymentStrategy }}

## Triage

1. Check the current rollout: `kubectl -n {{ .Service.Namespace }} rollout status deploy/{{ .Service.Name }}`
2. Inspect recent events: `kubectl -n {{ .Service.Namespace }} get events --sort-by=.lastTimestamp`
3. Check pod health: `kubectl -n {{ .Service.Namespace }} get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name={{ .Service.Name }}`
4. Compare p99 latency and error rate against the SLO dashboard.
5. Check the latest image scan and deployment commit.

## Rollback

```bash
curl -X POST http://sentinel-api/api/v1/services/{{ .Service.Name }}/rollback
```

## Escalation

Page {{ .Service.Team }} if the SLO burn continues for more than 10 minutes or rollback fails.
